ronen Perspektive und eröffnen Einsichten in die verschiedenen Bedeutungsnuancen des Phänomens.  afunded by Backlisttransformation EOSC Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFake news. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aDigitale Medien. 4aFiktion. 4aGermanistik. 4aKommunikation. 4aKultur. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aMedientheorie. 4aMeinung. 4aSocial Media. 4aWahrheit. 4aWirklichkeit. 4aÖffentlichkeit. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCommunication.  aCultural History.  aCulture.  aDigital Media.  aFiction.  aGerman Literature.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedia Theory.  aMedia.  aOpinion.  aPublic Sphere.  aReality.  aSocial Media.  aTruth.1 aBastert, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBendheim, Amelie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBendheim, Amelie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBonnet, Anne-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEgelhofer, Jana Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerz, Lina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofmann, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuemer, Birgit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMein, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOschema, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaganini, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPavlik, Jennifer, econ